news.title: China's Kaisa struggles for relief from bondholders as default risk looms
news.para: Kaisa's proposal to delay the maturity of the bond by 18 months comes against the backdrop of growing creditor concerns about Chinese property developers' ability to meet their near-term offshore repayment obligations.

news.title: More Chinese developers seek domestic bond issuance
news.para: Country Garden Real Estate Group, controlled by Country Garden Holdings, plans to issue medium-term notes worth 5 billion yuan. Chongqing Longhu Enterprise Development Co, the main platform of Longfor Group, plans to issue 3 billion yuan of debt.

news.title: MYRE Capital plans to raise Rs 150 crore by the end of March 2022
news.para: The company had recently raised Rs 31 crore through its offering in Times Square, Andheri, Mumbai. Spread across 17,817 sq ft, Times Square with a 5+5 year lock-in, is expected to offer a rental yield of 10.5%, and an Internal Rate of Return (IRR) of 13.6%.

news.title: IT department detects tax evasion worth crores after raids on Mumbai-based builder
news.para: The CBDT said in a statement on Thursday that the searches on the group, that undertakes construction of both residential and commercial projects, were launched on November 25 and about 30 premises were covered.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: Collectors told to speed up housing project work
news.para: The state government has planned the construction of about 31 lakh housing units spread over 17,000 colonies in two phases. The work on the first phase for construction of about 15 lakh housing units will be resumed immediately.

news.title: Stamp duty in Noida to be calculated as per carpet area
news.para: Super area of a flat is usually 20-25% more than the carpet area as it include area covered by the external walls, areas under services shafts, exclusive balcony or verandah area and exclusive open terrace area.

news.title: Input cost pressure to push cement prices to all-time high: Crisil
news.para: But the earnings before interest, tax, depreciation, and amortisation (Ebitda) of cement makers will decline by Rs 100-150 per tonne this fiscal because of high input costs. Cement sales volume is expected to rise 11-13% on-year this fiscal, albeit on a low base.

news.title: Gujarat government sanctions eight town planning schemes
news.para: These include five draft TP schemes in Ahmedabad, one draft TP scheme each in Bhavnagar and Rajkot and a preliminary TP scheme in Patan.

news.title: Minda Industries leases 47,867 sq ft office space in Pune
news.para: The duration for the lease is 15 years and it is a warm shell space, where the company will begin operations from January 2022 onwards.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: Village secretariats are now sub-registrar offices too
news.para: Governor Biswabhushan Harichandan issued the orders giving exemption to beneficiaries from user charges on sale deeds to be executed for the houses distributed under the flagship programme of One Time Settlement of the housing department.

news.title: Jaipur: JMC-Greater tails Heritage in providing lease deeds
news.para: While JMC-Heritage has issued 1,010 lease deeds, JMC-Greater has managed to issue 591 leases. JMC-Heritage has claimed that continuous work of officials had made it possible for them to grant so many lease deeds.

news.title: Ludhiana administration demolishes residential colony in Ladian Kalan area
news.para: He has urged the colonisers to adopt a legal way and get licenses from Greater Ludhiana Area Development Authority (GLADA) if they want to carry out their businesses in a hassle free manner.

news.title: Chandigarh administration okays adoption of model tenancy act
news.para: UT adviser Dharam Pal said that they have considered all objections and suggestions, and the file will soon be sent to UT administrator Banwarilal Purohit for final approval. The UT will then issue a final notification, he said.

news.title: Punjab & Haryana HC notice on plea to allow video conferencing for NRIs
news.para: The main issue before the HC is, “Whether the state of Haryana has such a robust system to take care of the genuine concerns of the citizens of India in these uncertain and prevalent Covid-19 times, especially when Indian courts are also working through electronic means?”

news.title: Building sites faced maximum penalties for pollution: HSPCB
news.para: Till now, HSPCB has imposed nearly Rs 2 crore penalties in its anti-pollution drive focussed on ensuring a complete ban on construction, diesel generator sets, wrongly parked vehicles and vehicles running without pollution under control (PUC) certificates.
